</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub138.ezboard.com/bphoenixsnest.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deslin@phoenixsnest>Deslin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF9300>(11/18/03 12:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub138.ezboard.com/fphoenixsnestfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FFX-2</span><hr size=1> The world is wide open. You can go anywhere you want in the beginning. However to progress through the story, there are certain places that you must go that are marked on the maps. The story progresses also through missions you have to complete. <br>
<br>
The demo had a simple mission where you had to race up a ruined tower before another group got there. <br>
<br>
The sphere grid has been replaced by something more interesting. It's called the &quot;Dress Grid.&quot; Each character has new outfit changes that correspond to certain jobs. Some jobs include, warrior, gunner, thief, white mage, black mage, alchemist, gun mage, starting to sound familiar? There are over 12 jobs that each character can play as. Based on how much you use a job, you increase in skills and gain new abilities, very similar to XI. The replay value will be very high based on this new job system. You can go through the game specializing in 2 jobs and then play again with a different set of 2 jobs, or you can diversify your efforts. Of course each character has starting attributes that lead that character to be stronger in certain jobs than the other characters. <br>
<br>
I'm really looking forward to this game as well...Mario Kart for the GC came out today and I still have to play SSX3 and FFXI!!! AHHHH too many games not enough time!!! <p>Deslin - Tarutaru - 9WHM/7WAR/2THF - Phoenix server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub138.ezboard.com/bphoenixsnest.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lavarien>Lavarien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FF9300>(11/18/03 7:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub138.ezboard.com/fphoenixsnestfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FFX-2</span><hr size=1> The sphere grid from FFX really bothered me.  To me, it was too complex.  There are better ways to have the player have to make strategic decisions than mind-numbingly getting points and finding spheres to advance each character, then find out you made a wrong turn somewhere and have to back-track.<br>
<br>
I also did not like FFVII or FFVIII's systems either.  Too much customization; everyone could do everything.  I like systems similar FFVI (granted, everyone could learn every magic spell eventually) and FFIX (everyone had unique abilities).<br>
<br>
So, I don't imagine I'll enjoy FFX-2 very much, and probably won't be getting it.<br>
<br>
I am enjoying Mario Kart Double-Dash, though.  Mario Kart 64 is still better. <p>~Lavarien~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub138.ezboard.com/bphoenixsnest.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stalkyrweaksoul>Stalkyr Weaksoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Micheavous...<BR>Deleterious...<BR>Frolicsome...<BR>Administrator!</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#FF9300>(11/19/03 9:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub138.ezboard.com/fphoenixsnestfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FFX-2</span><hr size=1> I liked FFX, but I would have preferred FFIX's system. I liked that every character had their own unique set of abilities.<br>
<br>
In FFX, I just had Tidus, Yuna, and Auron complete the grid. I figured out a way to get tons of AP fast (about 50 a per 5 min fight) so it was pretty easy.<br>
<br>
Even beat Nemesis <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Imho, FFIX and FFVI are my favorite games. I am loving FFXI though, but I honestly don't count it as part of the Final Fantasy series. I would have prefered they give the game it's own name, like Final Fantasy Online or something, rather than part of the numerical series.<br>
<br>
But that's just superficial, and I won't lose sleep over it. <p><CENTER><IMG SRC=http://stalksimages.homestead.com/15k.jpg><BR>
