<br>
But what you have to realize is, they're trying to make FFXI seem like a normal FF game (story sequences, etc.), but you can advance through the game (via internet) with other people.<br>
<br>
So, to me, it makes sense, but yet it doesn't , to call it FFXI. <p>~Lavarien~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub138.ezboard.com/bphoenixsnest.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deslin@phoenixsnest>Deslin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF9300>(11/20/03 12:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub138.ezboard.com/fphoenixsnestfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FFX-2</span><hr size=1> I just got the game yesterday and played through it for only a half hour...I knew if I kept playing I might not make it to work the next morning <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
It's pretty interesting the way they made the job system. It's really similar to ffxi job system but the great thing is that you can switch jobs mid-battle! <br>
<br>
The game starts out a little hokey and cheesy, but I think it gives the game a certain light heartedness it needs. The game graphics are great and I think I'm in love with Rikku <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I might have to put my ffxi efforts on hold for a little while o_o <p>Deslin - Tarutaru - 9WHM/7WAR/2THF - Phoenix server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub138.ezboard.com/bphoenixsnest.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lavarien>Lavarien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FF9300>(11/23/03 3:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub138.ezboard.com/fphoenixsnestfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FFX-2</span><hr size=1> Well, I bought the game out of an impulsive habit (FF name = good game, right?).<br>
<br>
It's actually quite different than I had imagined.  Advancing through the Job system is a lot like FFIX, more so than FFVII or FFVIII at least, because each Dress is like a piece of equipment you learn sills from.<br>
<br>
And the mission type-thing is fun, although I haven't done anything that didn't center around the storyline yet.  Battles are actually kinda fun now (but still way too many random encounters, IMO; I think random encounters should be for Currency and random items and Boss encounters give you Exp, but that's just me).<br>
<br>
The beginning, and random spots afterward, reminded me of Spice Girls, Charlie's Angels, and any other &quot;Girl Power&quot; thing you can think of, so the characters aren't that appealing to me (although Brother and Shinra are comical).<br>
<br>
